          <div data-content-element-selector="p, .js-buylink-item-container" data-allowed-classes-selector="js-buylink-item-container">
                <p>There has yet to be an official announcement for an <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/games/assassins-creed-iv-black-flag/">Assassin's Creed 4: Black Flag</a> remake, but the biggest hint of its existence may have been leaked on a Pure Arts livestream.</p><p>As reported by <a href="https://insider-gaming.com/assassins-creed-black-flag-remake-hinted/" data-target="true" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">Insider Gaming</a>, the stream happened back in March when the merchandising company revealed new ⅛ scale statues of characters from the Assassin's Creed series, though fans soon pointed out the absence of Edward Kenway from Black Flag.</p>



    
