      </div>
<p>At this, there appeared to be confusion as one of the hosts replied, "Assassin’s Creed fans out there, you should be aware that there is something going on with Edward [Keyway],” only for the other host to interrupt and ask, "Wait, has that been announced?"</p><p>The host continues, “I think so, I’m pretty sure I saw rumors about it. No, I definitely saw at article about it … So there’s going to be something going on with Edward, and our PVC ⅛ scale statue will reflect that accordingly."</p><p>From the confusion in this exchange, it would suggest that a statue is not being made yet because the character's appearance has been changed in a remake.</p><p>If the remake is coming, it's not clear whether Ubisoft will be announcing it at <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/articles/summer-game-conference-schedule-2025/1100-6531627/" data-ref-id="1100-6531627">Summer Game Fest</a> as Ubisoft Forward is not taking place this year. The publisher is however confirmed to have an appearance at the PC Gaming Show.</p><p>Rumors of a remake of the 2013 game had been swirling back in 2023, where the project was still <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/articles/assassins-creed-4-black-flag-remake-is-reportedly-coming/1100-6515623/" data-ref-id="1100-6515623">reportedly in early development</a>, while Skull and Bones developer Ubisoft Singapore was said to be heavily involved.</p>
  
                        
    
        
        
  
