            <title><![CDATA[Lego Helldivers 2 Super Destroyer Is Ready To Defend Super Earth In All Its 10,000 Piece Glory]]></title>
            <link>https://www.gamespot.com/articles/lego-helldivers-2-super-destroyer-is-ready-to-defend-super-earth-in-all-its-10000-piece-glory/1100-6531999/?ftag=CAD-01-10abi2f</link>
            <guid>https://www.resetera.com/threads/lego-helldivers-2-super-destroyer-is-ready-to-defend-super-earth-in-all-its-10-000-piece-glory.1204995/</guid>
            <content:encoded><![CDATA[https://www.gamespot.com/articles/lego-helldivers-2-super-destroyer-is-ready-to-defend-super-earth-in-all-its-10000-piece-glory/1100-6531999/?ftag=CAD-01-10abi2f<br/><br/><div id="readability-page-1" class="page"><p>
    <span data-nosnippet="">GameSpot may receive revenue from affiliate and advertising partnerships for sharing this content and from purchases through links.</span>
  </p><article itemscope="" data-type-id="1100" data-guid="1100-6531999">

            
            
  


        

  


        
        
              <section>

                  
          <div data-content-element-selector="p, .js-buylink-item-container" data-allowed-classes-selector="js-buylink-item-container">
                <p>A <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/games/helldivers-2/" data-ref-id="5000-589428">Helldivers 2</a> fan has gone above and beyond to honor Super Earth, constructing a Lego Super Destroyer so impressive it would bring a tear to the eye of democracy herself.</p><p dir="ltr">While <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/articles/helldivers-2-players-need-to-kill-2-5-billion-aliens-to-defend-super-earth-and-thats-just-the-start/1100-6531687/" data-ref-id="1100-6531687">Helldivers 2 players were prepping to defend Super Earth</a> from a full-on Illuminate invasion, creator ruralbricks on Instagram was building their own Lego Super Destroyer. In a <a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/Helldivers/comments/1kyjua5/super_earth_is_under_attack_built_the_lego_super/" data-target="true" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">post</a> on the Helldivers subreddit, ruralbricks broke down the stats behind the build, which they said took five months of work.</p><p dir="ltr">The Lego Super Destroyer is roughly 1:150 scale compared to the ones players command in Helldivers 2, but that doesn't mean the creation is small. It's over 4.5 feet in length, weighs 28 pounds, and consists of over 10,000 individual pieces. The build can even be broken down into five separate components for transport.</p><p dir="ltr">From the name emblazoned on the side (the SES Leviathan of Glory) to the launching Hellpods that can be seen below, the attention to detail in ruralbrick's creation is enough for any Helldiver to salivate over. More behind-the-scenes looks at the Lego Super Destroyer's creation can be seen over on ruralbrick's <a href="https://www.instagram.com/ruralbricks/" data-target="true" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">Instagram</a>.</p><p dir="ltr">While the fan-build won't likely ever become an official Lego product (it's much too large and would be far too expensive to be submitted to <a href="https://ideas.lego.com/" data-target="true" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">Lego Ideas</a>), fans in the comments are already asking for instructions on how to build their own. Ruralbricks seems open to the idea of potentially creating a smaller, more manageable version as well.</p><p dir="ltr">Perhaps inspired in a small part by ruralbricks' awe-inspiring creation, the <a href="https://www.ign.com/articles/helldivers-2-declares-victory-the-battle-of-super-earth-is-won-what-next-for-the-illuminate" data-target="true" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">Helldivers recently successfully defended Super Earth's Mega Cities</a> from attack, the latest chapter in Helldivers 2's ongoing multiplayer saga.</p>
  
                        
    
        
        
  
